.TH "bnx2i_alloc_qp_resc" 9 "bnx2i_alloc_qp_resc" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
bnx2i_alloc_qp_resc \- allocates required resources for QP.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" bnx2i_alloc_qp_resc
.BI "(struct bnx2i_hba *hba "  ","
.BI "struct bnx2i_endpoint *ep "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "hba" 12
adapter structure pointer
.IP "ep" 12
endpoint (transport identifier) structure
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Allocate QP (transport layer for iSCSI connection) resources, DMA'able
memory for SQ/RQ/CQ and page tables. EP structure elements such
as producer/consumer indexes/pointers, queue sizes and page table
contents are setup
